summary: Had a challenging 2-hour interview at Philips. Initially felt defeated due to negative feedback on problem-solving, but received a call from HR with encouragement to prepare harder for the next rounds.

wins: Persevered through a difficult interview that went an hour over schedule.
Received a positive call from HR to advance to the next round.
Didn't give up, even when feeling defeated mid-interview.
losses: Received critical negative feedback on problem-solving skills.
Felt sad and hopeless immediately following the interview.
ideas: Focus future prep specifically on the areas of problem-solving where I struggled.

goals: Prepare more effectively for the next interview round at Philips.
